God grants deliverances to sinners (in answer to prayers) who take His compassion as a sign that He approves of their ignorance and idols of the heart, but God is a God of knowledge and before Him actions are weighed: blessed are they who walk by faith (Spirit) not by sight (flesh) for His mercy rests upon His covenant.

1 Peter 3:12 For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and His ears are open unto their PRAYERS: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.

Man takes by force of principle that which he desires that flows with his aspiration but God's principle is superior and brings all things into subjection to Himself by His judgments. Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.

The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.

group.description:
Brothers and Sisters in Christ, I‚Äôm @shooglenifty and my fellow administrator is @libertyordeath777. 

God is good and His mercy endures forever!
***
By posting you are agreeing to our posting standards. We will remove a post that doesn't follow the guidelines below.
***
My hopes for the group is to foster phileo between the Christian diaspora that has chosen to join this group. We want to be a place where unbelievers come for answers and believers come to be bolstered in their faith. By the grace of God through the blood of Jesus we will bring His love to multitudes. My reasoning? I believe this: "Never doubt God‚Äôs mighty power to work in you and accomplish all this. He will achieve infinitely more than your greatest request, your most unbelievable dream, and exceed your wildest imagination! He will outdo them all, for his miraculous power constantly energizes you.‚ÄùEphesians 3:20 TPT
***
PLEASE READ BEFORE POSTING:
Posts that are encouraged (think ENGAGEMENT! and WHAT IS GOD TELLING YOU!):
1. Testimonies, praise reports, prayer requests, encouragements, prophecies, words from God, exhortations, etc.
2. Questions of those looking to our community for answers that only God can give.
3. Sermons, articles, videos, pictures and verses as long as they have a good description outlining who, what, where, why and how. If you don't respect the link you are posting or the other Christians in the group enough to take some time with your post, please don't post it. 
***
It seems most just post and run (seagull posting) and this is not God's heart nor mine. This group has ONE timeline. It also has many members. Is it respectful on your part to post several one line posts in a row pushing someone else's well thought post or plea out of sight of the group? With that in mind the following types of posts will be removed at the sole discretion of the moderators:
1. Off topic posts: politics, begging for followers or money, promoting personal agendas, etc.
2. Intentionally divisive, disrespectful or racist posts
3. Low effort (Just posting a video/link is not sufficient within the group, you must also write YOUR OWN description of the link/video; the included video/link description is not acceptable) or multiple posts in a row (limit of 2 posts per 3 hours)
4. Posts that don't meet the criteria mentioned above
5. Any reposts from other groups that are unrelated to Christianity; reposts of posts already in the group timeline (if you agree with a post just say it in the original post); and any reposts of your disagreements within a post brought to the group timeline.
6. Anyone who spams the same post to multiple groups (yes, I check timelines)
7. All members who block the administrators and moderators will be removed.
***
Remember that we are the body of Christ. Please keep your posts in line with Philippians 4:8 (ESV): Finally brothers, whatever is true, whatever is honorable, whatever is just, whatever is pure, whatever is lovely, whatever is commendable, if there is any excellence, if there is anything worthy of praise, think (post!) about these things.
***
‚ÄúThe Lord bless you and keep you; the Lord make his face to shine upon you and be gracious to you; the Lord lift up his countenance upon you and give you peace. ‚ÄúSo shall they put my name upon the people of Israel, and I will bless them.‚Äù‚ÄùNumbers 6:24-27 ESV

_source.contentraw:
God grants deliverances to sinners (in answer to prayers) who take His compassion as a sign that He approves of their ignorance and idols of the heart, but God is a God of knowledge and before Him actions are weighed: blessed are they who walk by faith (Spirit) not by sight (flesh) for His mercy rests upon His covenant.

1 Peter 3:12 For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and His ears are open unto their PRAYERS: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.

Man takes by force of principle that which he desires that flows with his aspiration but God's principle is superior and brings all things into subjection to Himself by His judgments. Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.

The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.

Through contact with Jesus, we put our efforts into building the house of God after the blueprint given to the steward of this season, Apostle Eric, even as God gave the blueprint for the tabernacle to Moses who oversaw this construction work, likewise, those in the house of Eva are building God's house under close supervision and oversight of God's steward in this Second 8th Week.

God did not change but man's heart has changed towards God. From faith to need.

God's purpose through Christ is for the salvation of those who acknowledge and mold with the instruction received through stewardship and submit themselves wholly to the process of salvation.

#S8W #Assembly #sunday #grace #apostle #apostolic #Jesus

group.description:
Fidem et Dialecticus. 

The Logos is a self-referential, self-similar, quasi-crystaline, geometric 9th-dimensional hyper-structure that is at the most fundamental basis of time and space; which is to say that it is time and space, so to study The Logos is to study the Mind of God. I think that it also is The Kingdom of Heaven Within, refered to by Jesus Christ, therefore it is the Union between Science and Christianity. It is God's Transcendent Universal Reason revealed as Enlightened Wisdom.

In this Denomination, in addition to standard Christian practices, one would attempt to figure out how observed scientific and logical data and classifications fit into conformance with The New Testament. So, we would look at the chapters that talked about a specific topic, and then work to make sense of the observed data by logical means, applied rigorously, to see how it may be in conformance with what is already written in The New Testament. That's the whole point. This group is intended to use Logic, rigorously, to look at science, archaeology, and other _hard data_ from a Christian perspective. 

It is not about that airy-fairy New Age bullshit. When considering a hypothesis, language should be used to clarify that it is a hypothesis, merely. This isn't about creativity so much as processing and synthesizing data.

As an example of what I mean: The Story of The Flood has been corroborated by data in the last decade regarding a Meteor Impact on Greenland approximately 12,000 years ago, which would have melted a vast amount of ice, causing a global flood as the ocean level raised by possibly hundreds of feet, rapidly, in just weeks or months. Applying Logic to scientific data from a Christian perspective.

The New Testament, which I call The Christian Bible, is that which I keep covanents with, adhere to, and constantly seek to increase my understanding of. The Old Testament, being the Jewish Bible, is not, however. I know the Jewish Bible to not be a historically reliable source of information, most of the time, based on the evidence.

Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.

The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.

Through contact with Jesus, we put our efforts into building the house of God after the blueprint given to the steward of this season, Apostle Eric, even as God gave the blueprint for the tabernacle to Moses who oversaw this construction work, likewise, those in the house of Eva are building God's house under close supervision and oversight of God's steward in this Second 8th Week.

God did not change but man's heart has changed towards God. From faith to need.

God's purpose through Christ is for the salvation of those who acknowledge and mold with the instruction received through stewardship and submit themselves wholly to the process of salvation.

#S8W #Assembly #sunday #grace #apostole #apostolic

group.description:
This is a group for all Christians on Gab who choose to keep the seventh-day Sabbath (Seventh-Day Adventists, Seventh-Day Baptists, Messianic Jews, Torah Observant, etc).

Why do we observe the seventh-day Sabbath?
The specific reasons vary, but generally we hold that the Fourth Commandment, written in stone, was never abolished or changed by Christ. Jesus/Yeshua/Messiah spoke often about how to keep the Sabbath, but throughout His life, and the rest of the New Testament, there is no Biblical command that changes the Sabbath day from the 7th to the 1st day of the week. Sunday observance in the Christian church has its origins in the pagan tradition of Sun worship and has no clear Scriptural foundation.

Christian Sabbath-Keepers choose to keep the seventh-day Sabbath holy in loving obedience to our Creator and Savior!

https://www.sabbathtruth.com https://www.seventhdaybaptist.org/sabbath https://brotherlance.com/commandment/ https://www.adventist.org/the-sabbath/the-sabbath-then-and-now

Group Rules: 1. Majority of your posts should be related to the Sabbath 2. Theological discussions welcome, personal attacks are not 3. Treat others in a Christ-like manner 4. Do not be intentionally divisive or hostile

Post that violate these rules will be removed and users who break these rules will be banned at the moderator's discretion. Tag @CT_Liberator in any posts that violate these rules for swift moderation.

Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.Through contact with Jesus, we put our efforts into building the house of God after the blueprint given to the steward of this season, Apostle Eric, even as God gave the blueprint for the tabernacle to Moses who oversaw this construction work, likewise, those in the house of Eva are building God's house under close supervision and oversight of God's steward in this Second 8th Week.God did not change but man's heart has changed towards God. From faith to need.God's purpose through Christ is for the salvation of those who acknowledge and mold with the instruction received through stewardship and submit themselves wholly to the process of salvation.#S8W #Assembly #sunday #grace #apostle #apostolic #Jesus #spiritual #tokens for #faith
_source.contentraw:
God grants deliverances to sinners (in answer to prayers) who take His compassion as a sign that He approves of their ignorance and idols of the heart, but God is a God of knowledge and before Him actions are weighed: blessed are they who walk by faith (Spirit) not by sight (flesh) for His mercy rests upon His covenant.

1 Peter 3:12 For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and His ears are open unto their PRAYERS: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.

Man takes by force of principle that which he desires that flows with his aspiration but God's principle is superior and brings all things into subjection to Himself by His judgments. Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.

The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.

Through contact with Jesus, we put our efforts into building the house of God after the blueprint given to the steward of this season, Apostle Eric, even as God gave the blueprint for the tabernacle to Moses who oversaw this construction work, likewise, those in the house of Eva are building God's house under close supervision and oversight of God's steward in this Second 8th Week.

God did not change but man's heart has changed towards God. From faith to need.

God's purpose through Christ is for the salvation of those who acknowledge and mold with the instruction received through stewardship and submit themselves wholly to the process of salvation.

#S8W #Assembly #sunday #grace #apostle #apostolic #Jesus #spiritual #tokens for #faith

group.description:
For Christian believers who desire relationships with other believers, want to share meals together, pray together, and worship Christ together in a non-religious setting. I wanted to create a way for those that can no longer be a part of the traditional, feminized, business church model to easily connect with one another in their own locality. Getting the church back to Ekklesia.

*Please make your posts relevant to house/home church.

**Feel free to post your location if you‚Äôre looking to connect with other believers in your area.

group.description:
Evangelical Christianity is a cross-denominational (One Lord, One Faith, One Baptism) belief in the biblical truths that: 1) Born Again Salvation comes only by Grace, through Faith in the Sacrificial Atonement of Jesus, the Messiah; 2) the Bible is the primary authority on matters of faith; and 3) the Great Commission is a living commandment to spread the Gospel to all people.
Believe that? You're Evangelical. Interested in learning more, or being a part of, this community of believers? Welcome.
https://gab.com/g/evangelical
Mirrored: https://mewe.com/join/evangelicalchristianity

* Let's be a most vibrant witness for God's Church here, and in the world.
* Keep it Christian related, Christ centered, and clean.
* Comment freely, but individually limit to 2 new posts per day. Quality over quantity.
* It is recommended that you switch to "New Post" or "Recent Activity" sort

Admin: @DocLance (be sure to follow all members and help build a community)

_source.contentraw:
God grants deliverances to sinners (in answer to prayers) who take His compassion as a sign that He approves of their ignorance and idols of the heart, but God is a God of knowledge and before Him actions are weighed: blessed are they who walk by faith (Spirit) not by sight (flesh) for His mercy rests upon His covenant.

1 Peter 3:12 For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and His ears are open unto their PRAYERS: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.

Man takes by force of principle that which he desires that flows with his aspiration but God's principle is superior and brings all things into subjection to Himself by His judgments. Thus, when the sinner frustrates grace by resisting grace, the Lord God that weighs the actions of man, frustrates the aspirations of sinners and resists the proud.

The righteous flow with the Spirit and resist not the grace of God for we know that grace is the power that sustains our faith even our soul.

Through contact with Jesus, we put our efforts into building the house of God after the blueprint given to the steward of this season, Apostle Eric, even as God gave the blueprint for the tabernacle to Moses who oversaw this construction work, likewise, those in the house of Eva are building God's house under close supervision and oversight of God's steward in this Second 8th Week.

God did not change but man's heart has changed towards God. From faith to need.

God's purpose through Christ is for the salvation of those who acknowledge and mold with the instruction received through stewardship and submit themselves wholly to the process of salvation.

#S8W #Assembly #sunday #grace #apostle #apostolic #Jesus #believe

group.description:
Building-up our most holy faith with testimonies, from saints of old & saints today, scripture, etc. Ministry of the Holy Spirit. Holy Spirit, FILL THIS PLACE & FILL US! MOVE FREELY, COME LORD! IN JESUS NAME. WE WANT YOU GOD! Precious Holy Spirit, have your way. We surrender to who you are. 

1 Cor. 12:27-31
You, then, are the body of Christ. Every one of you is a member of it. Furthermore, God has set-up in the church first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracle-workers, healers, assistants, administrators, and those who speak in tongues. Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Do all work miracles or have the gift of healing? Do all speak in tongues, all have the gift of interpretation of tongues? Set your hearts on the greater gifts.
1 Cor. 13:1-13 
Now I will show you the way which surpasses all the others. If I speak with human tongues and Angelic as well, but do not have love, I am a noisy gong, a clanging cymbal, if I have the gift of Prophecy and, with full knowledge, comprehend all Mysteries, if I have faith great enough to move mountains, but have not love, I am nothing. If I give everything I have to feed the poor and hand over my body to be burned, but have not love, I gain nothing. Love is patient; love is kind. Love is not jealous, it does not put on airs, it is not snobbish. Love is never rude, it is not self-seeking, it is not prone to anger; neither does it brood over injuries. Love does not rejoice in what is wrong but rejoices with the truth. There is no limit to Love's forbearance, to its trust, it's hope, its power to endure. Love Never Fails. Prophecies will cease, tongues will be silent, knowledge will pass away. Our knowledge is imperfect and our prophesying is imperfect. When the perfect comes, the imperfect will pass away. When I was a child I used to talk like a child, think like a child, reason like a child. When I became a man I put childish ways aside. Now we see indistinctly, as in a mirror; then we shall see face to face. My knowledge is imperfect now; then I shall know even as I am known. There are in the end three things that last: faith, hope, and love, and the greatest of these is love.
group.title: Supernatural Christianity

group.description: ‚ÄûWir wollen hier nicht erst in eine schwerf√§llige publizistische Definition des Krieges hineinsteigen, sondern uns an das Element desselben halten, an den Zweikampf. Der Krieg ist nichts als ein erweiterter Zweikampf. Wollen wir uns die Unzahl der einzelnen Zweik√§mpfe, aus denen er besteht, als Einheit denken, so tun wir besser, uns zwei Ringende vorzustellen. Jeder sucht den anderen durch physische Gewalt zur Erf√ºllung seines Willens zu zwingen; sein n√§chster Zweck ist, den Gegner niederzuwerfen und dadurch zu jedem ferneren Widerstand unf√§hig zu machen. Der Krieg ist also ein Akt der Gewalt, um den Gegner zur Erf√ºllung unseres Willens zu zwingen. Die Gewalt r√ºstet sich mit den Erfindungen der K√ºnste und Wissenschaften aus, um der Gewalt zu begegnen. Unmerkliche, kaum nennenswerte Beschr√§nkungen, die sie sich selbst setzt unter dem Namen v√∂lkerrechtlicher Sitte, begleiten sie, ohne ihre Kraft wesentlich zu schw√§chen. Gewalt, d. h. die physische Gewalt (denn eine moralische gibt es au√üer dem Begriffe des Staates und Gesetzes nicht), ist also das Mittel, dem Feinde unseren Willen aufzudringen, der Zweck. Um diesen Zweck sicher zu erreichen, m√ºssen wir den Feind wehrlos machen, und dies ist dem Begriff nach das eigentliche Ziel der kriegerischen Handlung. Es vertritt den Zweck und verdr√§ngt ihn gewisserma√üen als etwas nicht zum Kriege selbst Geh√∂riges.‚Äú (Carl von Clausewitz, ‚ÄûVom Kriege‚Äú)

Open Letter to BC CMOH Dr. Bonnie Henry to Rescind Vaccine Mandate for Health Professionals

From the Canadian Covid Care Alliance (CCCA) website: ‚ÄúMembers of the CCCA‚Äôs Scientific and Medical Committee have written an open letter to Dr. Bonnie Henry asking her to rescind the Order requiring B.C. health professionals to disclose their COVID-19 vaccination status. The letter includes numerous referenced statements about natural immunity, unvaccinated people, and their infectivity.‚Äù

The letter open letter is dated Aug. 10, 2022, and was sent to Henry, B.C.‚Äôs Chief Medical Officer of Health (CMOH), shortly thereafter. Henry has been exposed to have known about Covid injection adverse events, including deaths, through a series of emails obtained through an freedom of information request, while repeatedly claiming the unscientific mantra of ‚Äúsafe and effective.‚Äù

Will Henry continue to ignore the evidence presented in the letter or will she continue to compromise the health, safety and rights of B.C. health professionals?

The authors of the letter include:

Dr. Philip Britz-McKibbin, PhD, Professor, Dept. of Chemistry and Chemical Biology, McMaster University
Dr. Claudia Chaufan, MD, PhD, Associate Professor, Health Policy and Global Health, York University
Dr. Maria Gutschi, BSc Pharm, Pharm D, Pharmacy Consultant, ex-Scientific Officer
Dr. Ondrej Halgas, MSc, PhD, Biomedical research and structural biology
Dr. John Hardie, BDS, MSc, PhD, FRCDC, Oral pathologist (retired), former Head of the Department of Dentistry at the Vancouver General Hospital
Dr. York Hsiang, MB, MHSc, FRCSC, Professor, Dept. of Surgery, University of B.C.
Dr. Niel Karrow, PhD, Professor of Immunology, Dept. of Animal Biosciences, University of Guelph
Dr. Bonnie Mallard, Msc, PhD, Professor of Immunogenetics, Dept. of Pathobiology, University of Guelph
Dr. Bernard Massie, PhD, Microbiology and Immunology, former Director General of the Human Health Therapeutic Research Center of the National Research Council
Dr. Kanji Nakatsu, PhD, Professor Emeritus, Pharmacology, Queen‚Äôs University
Dr. Susan Natsheh, MD, Pediatrician (retired)
Dr. Philip R. Oldfield, DPhil, CSci, CChem, FRSC (UK) (retired)
Dr. Eric T. Payne, MD, MPH, FRCPC, Pediatric neurologist and Clinical Assistant Professor, University of Calgary
Dr. Steven Pelech, Professor, Department of Medicine, University of B.C.; President and Chief Scientific Officer, Kinexus Bioinformatics Corporation
